{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018HYCXVLrTCs1u8M8ymUWfj","type":"tool_result","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 7)\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable to `StackName[]`.\n- **Risk:** `recoverCorruptedState()` recovery path not directly unit-tested for `stacks` field — would need planted `package.json` in temp dir.\n- **Observation:** 19 new tests added, all 3098 tests pass with 0 failures.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — code-review (2026-03-23T14:36Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `init-project.ts` never persisted multi-stacks to state file — only single root stack written. All `detectStacks()` results lost on init.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `writeState()` mutated caller's state object via `state.stack = state.stacks[0]` side effect.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `isValidState()` accepted `stacks: [42, true]` as valid — no element type checking.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` produced inconsistent `stack: null` / `stacks: ['nodejs']` state.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `migrateState()` casts `raw.stack as StackName` without validating against known stack names.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `recoverCorruptedState()` calls both `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` — detection runs twice.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Flaky test in `sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts > writeStateAtomic` — shared file race condition under parallel execution.\n- **Coverage gap:** `init-project.test.ts` has zero assertions on `stacks` field after init. No test for recovery when root null but subdirs have stacks.\n\n---\n\n# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n\n### 10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry — create-story (2026-03-24T07:41Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Epic says StackName/AppType in `src/types/state.ts` but they actually live in `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`. Fixed in story.\n- **Implicit dependency:** AC3 requires stub NodejsProvider but epic puts full impl in story 10-2. Added minimal stub task.\n- **Risk:** Registry `detectStacks()` will coexist with existing `stack-detect.ts` `detectStacks()` during transition.\n- **Observation:** `patchStartScript?` optional method not in AC1 checklist but should be in interface definition.\n\n### 10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry — dev-story (2026-03-24T07:44Z)\n\n- **Parallel detection codepaths:** `stack-detect.ts` retains hardcoded detection; `registry.ts` has marker-based detection. Two codepaths coexist until story 10-5 migrates consumers.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors:** ~10 test files have unrelated compilation errors (bridge, run, stack, status, teardown, deps, sync).\n- **Code quality note:** Registry uses module-level Map state. Auto-registration in `index.ts` ensures NodejsProvider is registered on import, but direct `registry.ts` imports skip auto-registration.\n- **Test results:** 30 new tests pass, 79 existing stack-detect tests pass (backward compat confirmed).\n\n### 10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry — code-review (2026-03-24T07:50Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` at 0% coverage — barrel file with auto-registration never tested. Added index.test.ts.\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` at 17.64% coverage — 13 stub methods never called. Added nodejs.test.ts.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Bare `catch {}` in registry.ts line 73 — readdirSync errors silently swallowed.\n- **MEDIUM (not fixed):** `StackDetection` type duplicated between registry.ts and stack-detect.ts. Deferred to story 10-5.\n- **MEDIUM (not fixed):** stack-detect.ts still has independent detection logic (not re-exported from registry). Expected per story scope.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `_resetRegistry` test-only utility leaking into public barrel export.\n- **Coverage:** 97.06% overall, all 127 files above 80% floor.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec2bf7d9-1cd3-4665-9804-65790a3eadb3","uuid":"650c1ca5-db4a-49e9-b31c-a410ed09527f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:55:31.323Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23 (session 7)\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — create-story (2026-03-23T14:24Z)\n\n- **Ambiguity:** Epic says `stacks: string[]` but `StackName` union type exists from story 9-1. Chose `StackName[]` for type safety.\n- **Missing context:** `InitResult` in `types.ts` may need `stacks` field but epic FR4 doesn't explicitly call it out — implied by scope.\n- **Risk:** `detectStacks()` can return duplicate stack names from multiple directories. `stacks` field needs deduplication.\n- **Observation:** All 8 ACs are cli-verifiable via unit tests — no external dependencies.\n\n### 9-2-state-schema-migration-multi-stack — dev-story (2026-03-23T14:32Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing type errors:** `bridge.test.ts` implicit `any`, `run.test.ts` spread arg type error, `stack.test.ts` missing `endpoint`, `status.test.ts` missing `timeoutSummary`. None from this story.\n- **Workaround:** Used `stacks: ['nodejs'] as StackName[]` instead of `as const` in `stack.test.ts` because readonly tuples aren't assignable