{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AM3W7PCLsWH4AYSDEgiuBD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→stepsCompleted: [1]\n     3→inputDocuments:\n     4→  - architecture-operational-excellence.md\n     5→  - architecture-overhaul.md\n     6→  - architecture.md\n     7→  - tech-spec-retro-pipeline-harness-fixes.md\n     8→  - tech-spec-rust-stack-support.md\n     9→  - tech-spec-multi-stack-support.md\n    10→  - session-retro-2026-03-23.md\n    11→  - session-retro-2026-03-24.md\n    12→  - .session-issues.md\n    13→workflowType: 'architecture'\n    14→project_name: 'codeharness'\n    15→user_name: 'BMad'\n    16→date: '2026-03-24'\n    17→---\n    18→\n    19→# Architecture Decision Document — v3 (Clean Rewrite)\n    20→\n    21→_Replaces architecture.md, architecture-overhaul.md, and architecture-operational-excellence.md. This is the single authoritative architecture document for codeharness going forward._\n    22→\n    23→## Why a Rewrite\n    24→\n    25→The current architecture accumulated across 3 documents and 9 epics. It was never consolidated. The result:\n    26→- 12 files exceed the 300-line limit (worst: 832 lines)\n    27→- 5 state files with no sync mechanism\n    28→- 41 stack conditionals across 8 files (no abstraction)\n    29→- 28 files coupled to Ralph with no interface\n    30→- 53 bare `catch {}` blocks swallowing errors\n    31→- 155 `Record<string, unknown>` casts eroding type safety\n    32→- Two parallel template systems\n    33→- Command files containing business logic\n    34→\n    35→This document defines the target architecture. Migration from current to target is incremental — not a big-bang rewrite.\n    36→\n    37→---\n    38→\n    39→## Project Context\n    40→\n    41→### What Codeharness Is\n    42→\n    43→A CLI tool + Claude Code plugin that provides autonomous sprint execution for software projects. It detects the project's tech stack, sets up observability, executes stories through a create→dev→review→verify pipeline, and enforces quality gates.\n    44→\n    45→### Distribution Channels\n    46→\n    47→1. **Claude Code plugin** — installed via `claude plugin install`. Ships: `commands/`, `hooks/`, `skills/`, `knowledge/`\n    48→2. **npm package** — installed via `npm install -g codeharness`. Ships: `dist/`, `templates/`, `ralph/`\n    49→\n    50→Both channels must version-sync. CI enforces `plugin.json` ↔ `package.json` version match.\n    51→\n    52→### Supported Stacks\n    53→\n    54→Node.js, Python, Rust. Future: Go, Java. Architecture must make adding a stack a single-file operation.\n    55→\n    56→---\n    57→\n    58→## Core Architectural Decisions\n    59→\n    60→### Decision 1: Unified State — One File, Versioned Schema\n    61→\n    62→**Problem:** 5+ state files (`sprint-state.json`, `sprint-status.yaml`, `codeharness.local.md`, `.story_retries`, `.flagged_stories`) with no sync mechanism. Every session has desync bugs. State readers and writers are scattered across 15+ files.\n    63→\n    64→**Decision:** Consolidate into **two** state files with clear ownership:\n    65→\n    66→| File | Purpose | Format | Owner |\n    67→|------|---------|--------|-------|\n    68→| `.claude/codeharness.local.md` | **Project config** — stack, enforcement, OTLP, coverage targets | YAML frontmatter + markdown | `src/lib/state.ts` |\n    69→| `sprint-state.json` | **Sprint runtime** — story statuses, retries, flags, run progress, observability coverage | JSON | `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` |\n    70→\n    71→**What gets consolidated INTO sprint-state.json:**\n    72→- `sprint-status.yaml` → `sprint-state.json` field `stories: Record<string, StoryState>` (sprint-status.yaml becomes a derived view, generated from sprint-state.json for human readability)\n    73→- `.story_retries` → `sprint-state.json` field `retries: Record<string, number>`\n    74→- `.flagged_stories` → `sprint-state.json` field `flagged: string[]`\n    75→- `ralph/status.json` → `sprint-state.json` field `session: { ... }`\n    76→\n    77→**What stays in codeharness.local.md:**\n    78→- Stack detection results (stacks, app types)\n    79→- Enforcement flags (frontend, database, api)\n    80→- OTLP config (backend, endpoint, service name)\n    81→- Coverage config (target, baseline)\n    82→- Docker config\n    83→\n    84→**Schema versioning:**\n    85→```typescript\n    86→interface SprintState {\n    87→  version: 2;  // Increment on schema changes\n    88→  stories: Record<string, StoryState>;\n    89→  retries: Record<string, number>;\n    90→  flagged: string[];\n    91→  epics: Record<string, EpicState>;\n    92→  session: SessionState;\n    93→  observability: ObservabilityState;\n    94→  run: RunProgress;\n    95→}\n    96→```\n    97→\n    98→**Migration:** `readSprintState()` checks `version` field. If missing or < current, runs migration chain. Old files (`.story_retries`, `.flagged_stories`) are read during migration, then deleted.\n    99→\n   100→**Derived views:**\n   101→- `sprint-status.yaml` is GENERATED from `sprint-state.json` after each write. It's a human-readable view, not a source of truth. `readSprintStatus()` becomes `generateSprintStatusYaml()`.\n   102→- The Ink renderer reads `sprint-state.json` directly (no more polling sprint-status.yaml).\n   103→\n   104→**Atomic writes:** All state writes use `writeFileSync` to a temp file + `renameSync` (atomic on POSIX). Already established in sprint module — now enforced everywhere.\n   105→\n   106→---\n   107→\n   108→### Decision 2: Stack Provider Pattern — Add a Language = Add One File\n   109→\n   110→**Problem:** 41 if/else branches on `stack === 'nodejs' | 'python' | 'rust'` across 8 files. Adding Go means touching 8+ files. No abstraction.\n   111→\n   112→**Decision:** Create a `StackProvider` interface. Each language implements it in one file. A registry maps stack names to providers.\n   113→\n   114→```typescript\n   115→// src/lib/stacks/types.ts\n   116→interface StackProvider {\n   117→  readonly name: StackName;\n   118→  readonly markers: string[];           // Files that identify this stack (e.g., ['package.json'])\n   119→  readonly displayName: string;         // 'Node.js (package.json)'\n   120→\n   121→  detectAppType(dir: string): AppType;\n   122→  getCoverageTool(): CoverageToolName;\n   123→  detectCoverageConfig(dir: string): CoverageToolInfo;\n   124→  getOtlpPackages(): string[];\n   125→  installOtlp(dir: string): OtlpResult;\n   126→  patchStartScript?(dir: string): boolean;\n   127→  getDockerfileTemplate(): string;\n   128→  getDockerBuildStage(): string;\n   129→  getRuntimeCopyDirectives(): string;\n   130→  getBuildCommands(): string[];\n   131→  getTestCommands(): string[];\n   132→  getSemgrepLanguages(): string[];\n   133→  parseTestOutput(output: string): TestCounts;\n   134→  parseCoverageReport(dir: string): number;\n   135→  getProjectName(dir: string): string | null;\n   136→}\n   137→```\n   138→\n   139→**File structure:**\n   140→```\n   141→src/lib/stacks/\n   142→├── types.ts          # StackProvider interface, StackName type, AppType\n   143→├── registry.ts       # Map<StackName, StackProvider>, detectStacks(), detectStack()\n   144→├── nodejs.ts         # NodejsProvider implements StackProvider\n   145→├── python.ts         # PythonProvider implements StackProvider\n   146→├── rust.ts           # RustProvider implements StackProvider\n   147→└── __tests__/\n   148→```\n   149→\n   150→**Adding Go:**\n   151→1. Create `src/lib/stacks/go.ts` implementing `StackProvider`\n   152→2. Register it in `registry.ts`: `registry.set('go', new GoProvider())`\n   153→3. Create `patches/observability/go-*.yaml` Semgrep rules\n   154→4. Create `templates/Dockerfile.verify.go`\n   155→5. Done. Zero changes to coverage.ts, otlp.ts, docs-scaffold.ts, etc.\n   156→\n   157→**Consumers change from:**\n   158→```typescript\n   159→if (stack === 'nodejs') { ... }\n   160→else if (stack === 'python') { ... }\n   161→else if (stack === 'rust') { ... }\n   162→```\n   163→**To:**\n   164→```typescript\n   165→const provider = getStackProvider(stack);\n   166→provider.detectCoverageConfig(dir);\n   167→```\n   168→\n   169→**Multi-stack:** `detectStacks()` stays in `registry.ts`. Returns `StackDetection[]`. Each detection carries a reference to its provider.\n   170→\n   171→---\n   172→\n   173→### Decision 3: Agent Abstraction — Ralph Becomes One Implementation\n   174→\n   175→**Problem:** 28 files reference Ralph directly. State files are written by bash, read by TypeScript. No versioned contract. If Ralph is replaced, 28 files break.\n   176→\n   177→**Decision:** Create an `AgentDriver` interface. Ralph becomes one implementation. Future drivers (direct Claude API, other LLM CLIs) can be added.\n   178→\n   179→```typescript\n   180→// src/lib/agents/types.ts\n   181→interface AgentDriver {\n   182→  readonly name: string;\n   183→  spawn(opts: SpawnOpts): AgentProcess;\n   184→  parseOutput(line: string): AgentEvent | null;\n   185→  getStatusFile(): string;\n   186→}\n   187→\n   188→interface AgentProcess {\n   189→  stdout: Readable;\n   190→  stderr: Readable;\n   191→  on(event: 'close', handler: (code: number) => void): void;\n   192→  kill(signal?: string): void;\n   193→}\n   194→\n   195→type AgentEvent =\n   196→  | { type: 'tool-start'; name: string }\n   197→  | { type: 'tool-complete'; name: string; args: string }\n   198→  | { type: 'text'; text: string }\n   199→  | { type: 'story-complete'; key: string; details: string }\n   200→  | { type: 'story-failed'; key: string; reason: string }\n   201→  | { type: 'iteration'; count: number }\n   202→  | { type: 'retry'; attempt: number; delay: number }\n   203→  | { type: 'result'; cost: number; sessionId: string };\n   204→```\n   205→\n   206→**File structure:**\n   207→```\n   208→src/lib/agents/\n   209→├── types.ts          # AgentDriver, AgentProcess, AgentEvent interfaces\n   210→├── ralph.ts          # RalphDriver implements AgentDriver (wraps ralph.sh)\n   211→├── stream-parser.ts  # Moved from src/lib/ — parses Claude stream-json\n   212→└── __tests__/\n   213→```\n   214→\n   215→**What changes:**\n   216→- `run.ts` imports `AgentDriver` instead of directly spawning ralph\n   217→- `run-helpers.ts` merges into `ralph.ts` (ralph-specific parsing)\n   218→- `ralph-prompt.ts` moves into `ralph.ts`\n   219→- State files (`.story_retries`, `.flagged_stories`) are managed by TypeScript, not bash\n   220→\n   221→**What ralph.sh keeps:**\n   222→- Loop execution (iteration management)\n   223→- Claude Code CLI invocation\n   224→- Timeout handling\n   225→- But it reads/writes state through a JSON protocol, not raw files\n   226→\n   227→---\n   228→\n   229→### Decision 4: lib/ Restructuring — Subdirectories with Facades\n   230→\n   231→**Problem:** `src/lib/` is a flat directory with 20+ files. No internal structure. Everything imports from everything. Coverage (617 lines), Docker (378 lines), OTLP (422 lines), beads (590 lines) — all monolithic.\n   232→\n   233→**Decision:** Restructure `src/lib/` into domain subdirectories with index.ts facades.\n   234→\n   235→```\n   236→src/lib/\n   237→├── stacks/           # Decision 2 — stack providers\n   238→│   ├── index.ts      # Re-exports: detectStack, detectStacks, getProvider\n   239→│   ├── types.ts\n   240→│   ├── registry.ts\n   241→│   ├── nodejs.ts\n   242→│   ├── python.ts\n   243→│   └── rust.ts\n   244→├── agents/           # Decision 3 — agent drivers\n   245→│   ├── index.ts\n   246→│   ├── types.ts\n   247→│   ├── ralph.ts\n   248→│   └── stream-parser.ts\n   249→├── coverage/         # Split from 617-line coverage.ts\n   250→│   ├── index.ts      # Re-exports: detectCoverageTool, runCoverage, evaluateCoverage\n   251→│   ├── types.ts      # CoverageToolInfo, CoverageResult, CoverageEvaluation\n   252→│   ├── runner.ts     # runCoverage, checkOnlyCoverage\n   253→│   ├── evaluator.ts  # evaluateCoverage, updateCoverageState\n   254→│   └── parser.ts     # parseTestCounts, parseCoverageReport (delegates to stack provider)\n   255→├── docker/           # Split from 378-line docker.ts\n   256→│   ├── index.ts\n   257→│   ├── compose.ts    # startStack, stopStack, startSharedStack\n   258→│   ├── health.ts     # getStackHealth, checkDocker\n   259→│   └── cleanup.ts    # cleanupOrphanedContainers, cleanupVerifyEnv\n   260→├── observability/    # OTLP config (not the observability module)\n   261→│   ├── index.ts\n   262→│   ├── instrument.ts # instrumentProject (delegates to stack provider)\n   263→│   ├── config.ts     # configureOtlpEnvVars, ensureServiceNameEnvVar\n   264→│   └── backends.ts   # Backend-specific query builders (Victoria, ELK)\n   265→├── sync/             # Split from 590-line beads-sync.ts\n   266→│   ├── index.ts\n   267→│   ├── beads.ts      # bdCommand, BeadsNotInstalledError\n   268→│   ├── sprint-yaml.ts # readSprintStatus (now generates from sprint-state.json)\n   269→│   └── story-files.ts # readStoryFileStatus, updateStoryFile\n   270→├── state.ts          # Project config (codeharness.local.md) — stays flat, <200 lines\n   271→├── output.ts         # CLI output helpers — stays flat, <50 lines\n   272→├── templates.ts      # Template file generation — stays flat, <50 lines\n   273→└── __tests__/        # Shared test utilities, fixtures\n   274→    ├── fixtures/     # Reusable test data (Cargo.toml variants, state files)\n   275→    └── helpers.ts    # Mock factories, state builders\n   276→```\n   277→\n   278→**Import rules:**\n   279→- External consumers import from `src/lib/{domain}/index.ts` only\n   280→- Within a domain, files can import from siblings\n   281→- No cross-domain internal imports (e.g., `coverage/runner.ts` cannot import from `docker/compose.ts` directly — go through `docker/index.ts`)\n   282→- `src/lib/state.ts` and `src/lib/output.ts` are shared utilities — any file can import them\n   283→\n   284→**Enforcement:** Add ESLint rule or boundary test that flags internal cross-domain imports.\n   285→\n   286→---\n   287→\n   288→### Decision 5: Observability Backend Choice — Victoria vs ELK vs Remote\n   289→\n   290→**Problem:** VictoriaMetrics hardcoded everywhere. Ports hardcoded. No way to use ELK or a remote endpoint.\n   291→\n   292→**Decision:** `codeharness init` asks for backend choice. Stored in state. All query builders and health checks dispatch on backend type.\n   293→\n   294→```typescript\n   295→// In codeharness.local.md state\n   296→interface OtlpConfig {\n   297→  enabled: boolean;\n   298→  backend: 'victoria' | 'elk' | 'none';\n   299→  mode: 'local-shared' | 'remote';\n   300→  endpoints: {\n   301→    otel: string;     // OTLP collector (default: http://localhost:4318)\n   302→    logs: string;     // Log query API (Victoria: :9428, ELK: :9200)\n   303→    metrics: string;  // Metric query API (Victoria: :8428, ELK: :9200)\n   304→    traces: string;   // Trace query API (Victoria: :16686, Jaeger/Zipkin)\n   305→  };\n   306→  service_name: string;\n   307→}\n   308→```\n   309→\n   310→**Backend-specific logic lives in `src/lib/observability/backends.ts`:**\n   311→```typescript\n   312→interface ObservabilityBackend {\n   313→  buildLogQuery(service: string, timeRange: string): string;\n   314→  buildMetricQuery(service: string, metric: string): string;\n   315→  buildTraceQuery(service: string, limit: number): string;\n   316→  getComposeFile(): string;\n   317→  getHealthCheck(): HealthCheckResult;\n   318→}\n   319→```\n   320→\n   321→Two implementations: `VictoriaBackend`, `ElkBackend`. Selected by `state.otlp.backend`.\n   322→\n   323→**Remote mode:** If `mode === 'remote'`, skip Docker compose entirely. Use provided endpoints. Health check pings the endpoints instead of checking containers.\n   324→\n   325→**Init flow:**\n   326→```\n   327→codeharness init\n   328→  → Stack detected: Node.js + Rust\n   329→  → Observability backend: [victoria] elk none\n   330→  → Mode: [local] remote\n   331→  → (if remote) Endpoints: otel=..., logs=..., metrics=..., traces=...\n   332→```\n   333→\n   334→---\n   335→\n   336→### Decision 6: Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline — Tech Debt as First-Class Work\n   337→\n   338→**Problem:** Session retros produce action items that never get actioned. Tech debt accumulates silently. No mechanism to feed retro findings back into the sprint.\n   339→\n   340→**Decision:** Three mechanisms embedded in the sprint cycle:\n   341→\n   342→**6a. Persistent epic-TD:**\n   343→- `epic-TD` in sprint-state.json is never marked `done`\n   344→- New stories append to it from any source (retro, audit, manual)\n   345→- harness-run Step 5 skips epic completion for `epic-TD`\n   346→\n   347→**6b. Retro auto-creates stories (Step 8b):**\n   348→- After session retro writes the markdown file, harness-run parses `## 6. Action Items`\n   349→- `### Fix Now` and `### Fix Soon` items become `TD-N-slug: backlog` stories\n   350→- Deduplication: normalize text, compare against existing TD story titles (80% word overlap = skip)\n   351→- `### Backlog` items go to `tech-debt-backlog.md` for tracking only\n   352→\n   353→**6c. Tech debt gate (Step 2 priority):**\n   354→- Before selecting ANY Tier D (backlog) story from a feature epic, check if `epic-TD` has pending work\n   355→- If yes, process TD stories first\n   356→- This ensures accumulated debt gets addressed before new features start\n   357→\n   358→---\n   359→\n   360→### Decision 7: Error Handling — No More Silent Swallowing\n   361→\n   362→**Problem:** 53 bare `catch {}` blocks. Errors are logged as comments but not propagated. Debugging is impossible because stack traces are lost.\n   363→\n   364→**Decision:** Three error strategies, no fourth:\n   365→\n   366→1. **Result\\<T\\>** for all module-level functions that can fail expectably (file not found, parse error, subprocess failure). Already established — enforce it.\n   367→\n   368→2. **Typed errors** for domain-specific failures:\n   369→```typescript\n   370→class BeadsNotInstalledError extends Error { ... }\n   371→class DockerNotAvailableError extends Error { ... }\n   372→class StateCorruptedError extends Error { ... }\n   373→class StackNotSupportedError extends Error { ... }\n   374→```\n   375→\n   376→3. **Explicit ignore with reason** for truly non-fatal cases:\n   377→```typescript\n   378→try { ... }\n   379→catch {\n   380→  // IGNORE: cleanup failure is non-fatal — container may already be removed\n   381→}\n   382→```\n   383→\n   384→**Banned:** `catch { }`, `catch { return null }`, `catch { /* fallthrough */ }` without an `// IGNORE:` comment explaining why.\n   385→\n   386→**Enforcement:** ESLint rule `no-empty-catch` + custom rule requiring `// IGNORE:` comment in catch blocks that don't rethrow or return Result.fail().\n   387→\n   388→---\n   389→\n   390→### Decision 8: Command Structure — Thin Commands, Fat Modules\n   391→\n   392→**Problem:** `status.ts` is 744 lines. Commands contain business logic (URL builders, formatters, story drill-down). Not testable without command wiring.\n   393→\n   394→**Decision:** Commands are <100 lines. They parse CLI args, call a module function, format output. All business logic lives in modules.\n   395→\n   396→```typescript\n   397→// src/commands/status.ts — THIN (< 100 lines)\n   398→export function registerStatusCommand(program: Command): void {\n   399→  program.command('status')\n   400→    .option('--check-docker', '...')\n   401→    .option('--story <key>', '...')\n   402→    .action(async (options) => {\n   403→      const result = await statusModule.getStatus(options);\n   404→      if (isOk(result)) {\n   405→        statusModule.formatOutput(result.data, options);\n   406→      } else {\n   407→        fail(result.error);\n   408→      }\n   409→    });\n   410→}\n   411→```\n   412→\n   413→**Business logic moves to:**\n   414→```\n   415→src/modules/status/\n   416→├── index.ts        # getStatus, formatOutput\n   417→├── formatters.ts   # Human-readable + JSON formatting\n   418→├── endpoints.ts    # URL builders (moved from status.ts)\n   419→└── drill-down.ts   # Story detail logic (moved from status.ts)\n   420→```\n   421→\n   422→**Same pattern for all commands >100 lines.** The command file is glue code. The module is testable independently.\n   423→\n   424→---\n   425→\n   426→### Decision 9: Template Unification — One System\n   427→\n   428→**Problem:** Two parallel template systems: TypeScript generators in `src/templates/` and static files in `templates/`. Unclear when to use which.\n   429→\n   430→**Decision:** All templates are static files in `templates/`. TypeScript code reads and interpolates them. No more generated-in-code templates.\n   431→\n   432→```\n   433→templates/\n   434→├── dockerfiles/\n   435→│   ├── Dockerfile.nodejs         # Was nodejsTemplate() in TS\n   436→│   ├── Dockerfile.python\n   437→│   ├── Dockerfile.rust\n   438→│   ├── Dockerfile.generic\n   439→│   ├── Dockerfile.verify         # Node.js verification\n   440→│   ├── Dockerfile.verify.rust\n   441→│   └── Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl  # Template with {STAGES} and {COPIES} placeholders\n   442→├── otlp/\n   443→│   ├── nodejs.md\n   444→│   ├── python.md\n   445→│   └── rust.md\n   446→├── compose/\n   447→│   ├── victoria.yml\n   448→│   ├── elk.yml\n   449→│   └── otel-collector-config.yaml\n   450→├── prompts/\n   451→│   ├── ralph-prompt.md           # Was ralph-prompt.ts\n   452→│   ├── verify-prompt.md          # Was verify-prompt.ts\n   453→│   └── showboat-template.md\n   454→└── docs/\n   455→    ├── readme.md.tmpl            # Was readme.ts\n   456→    └── agents.md.tmpl            # Was generateAgentsMdContent()\n   457→```\n   458→\n   459→**Interpolation:** A single `renderTemplate(path, vars)` function in `src/lib/templates.ts`. Variables use `{{var}}` syntax. No complex logic in templates — if logic is needed, the caller computes the value and passes it as a variable.\n   460→\n   461→**Multi-stage Dockerfile:** The `Dockerfile.multi-stage.tmpl` has `{{BUILD_STAGES}}` and `{{COPY_DIRECTIVES}}` placeholders. The caller composes build stages from per-stack templates and passes them.\n   462→\n   463→---\n   464→\n   465→### Decision 10: Verification Environment — Stack-Aware Provisioning\n   466→\n   467→**Problem:** Docker verify container under-provisioned for every project. Missing Rust version, system libs, clippy, tarpaulin. Fixed manually EVERY verification. PATH not inherited.\n   468→\n   469→**Decision:** Verification Dockerfile is generated per-project based on detected stacks, not selected from a static template.\n   470→\n   471→```typescript\n   472→// src/modules/verify/env.ts\n   473→function generateVerifyDockerfile(stacks: StackDetection[]): string {\n   474→  const sections: string[] = [];\n   475→\n   476→  // Base image\n   477→  sections.push('FROM ubuntu:22.04');\n   478→  sections.push('ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH\"');\n   479→\n   480→  // Common tools\n   481→  sections.push('RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl jq git python3 pipx');\n   482→  sections.push('RUN pipx install semgrep showboat');\n   483→\n   484→  // Per-stack tooling\n   485→  for (const detection of stacks) {\n   486→    const provider = getStackProvider(detection.stack);\n   487→    sections.push(provider.getVerifyDockerfileSection());\n   488→  }\n   489→\n   490→  // OTLP config\n   491→  sections.push('ENV OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:4318');\n   492→\n   493→  return sections.join('\\n\\n');\n   494→}\n   495→```\n   496→\n   497→Each `StackProvider` provides its verify Dockerfile section:\n   498→- **Rust:** Install rustup + stable toolchain + cargo-tarpaulin + clippy + system libs\n   499→- **Node.js:** Install Node.js + npm\n   500→- **Python:** Install pip + coverage\n   501→\n   502→The Dockerfile is generated at `verify-env build` time, not selected from a static file. This ensures it always matches the project's needs.\n   503→\n   504→---\n   505→\n   506→### Decision 11: Process Enforcement — Embedded Quality Gates\n   507→\n   508→**Problem:** Docker pre-check missing (wastes 30-min sessions). Subagents don't update status (reported 7+ times). Time budget ignored (3 sessions failed at verification). Architecture docs too large (>10k tokens).\n   509→\n   510→**Decision:** Five embedded gates in harness-run:\n   511→\n   512→| Gate | Where | What |\n   513→|------|-------|------|\n   514→| **Docker pre-check** | Step 1 pre-flight | `docker info` — fail fast if Docker not running |\n   515→| **Orphan cleanup** | Step 1 pre-flight | Remove leftover `codeharness-verify` containers |\n   516→| **State reconciliation** | Step 1 pre-flight | Rebuild sprint-state.json from sprint-status.yaml |\n   517→| **Time budget check** | Before each phase (3b, 3c, 3d) | Defer if remaining < estimated phase duration |\n   518→| **Status ownership** | After each subagent | Orchestrator owns all status writes — verify and fix |\n   519→\n   520→**Subagent status enforcement:** Remove all instructions that tell subagents to update sprint-status.yaml. Subagents are read-only on state. The orchestrator reads the subagent's output, determines the status transition, and writes it. This is the only reliable pattern.\n   521→\n   522→**Time budget awareness:**\n   523→```\n   524→Phase estimates:\n   525→  create-story: 5 min\n   526→  dev-story: 15 min\n   527→  code-review: 10 min\n   528→  verification: 20 min\n   529→  retro: 5 min\n   530→\n   531→Before each phase: if remaining_time < phase_estimate, defer.\n   532→```\n   533→\n   534→---\n   535→\n   536→### Decision 12: File Size Enforcement — CI Gate\n   537→\n   538→**Problem:** 12 files exceed 300 lines. Worst: 832 lines. The rule exists but nobody enforces it.\n   539→\n   540→**Decision:** Add a CI check that fails the build if any `.ts` file in `src/` exceeds 300 lines.\n   541→\n   542→```bash\n   543→# In CI pipeline, after build\n   544→find src -name '*.ts' -not -path '*__tests__*' -exec awk 'END{if(NR>300)print FILENAME\": \"NR\" lines\"}' {} \\; | tee /dev/stderr | grep -q . && exit 1\n   545→```\n   546→\n   547→**Existing violations get a migration path:** Each over-limit file gets a story in epic-TD to split it. The CI gate starts as a warning, becomes a hard failure after all files are under 300 lines.\n   548→\n   549→**Current violators and their target split:**\n   550→\n   551→| File | Lines | Split Into |\n   552→|------|-------|-----------|\n   553→| `doc-health.ts` | 832 | `doc-health/scanner.ts`, `doc-health/staleness.ts`, `doc-health/report.ts` |\n   554→| `status.ts` (command) | 744 | Move logic to `modules/status/` |\n   555→| `coverage.ts` | 617 | `coverage/runner.ts`, `coverage/evaluator.ts`, `coverage/parser.ts` |\n   556→| `beads-sync.ts` | 590 | `sync/beads.ts`, `sync/sprint-yaml.ts`, `sync/story-files.ts` |\n   557→| `bmad.ts` | 522 | `sync/bmad-bridge.ts`, `sync/epic-generator.ts` |\n   558→| `scanner.ts` | 447 | `scanner/file-scanner.ts`, `scanner/coverage-scanner.ts` |\n   559→| `otlp.ts` | 422 | `observability/instrument.ts`, `observability/config.ts` |\n   560→\n   561→---\n   562→\n   563→## Module Structure (Target)\n   564→\n   565→```\n   566→src/\n   567→├── commands/           # Thin command wiring (<100 lines each)\n   568→│   ├── init.ts\n   569→│   ├── run.ts\n   570→│   ├── status.ts\n   571→│   ├── audit.ts\n   572→│   ├── verify.ts\n   573→│   ├── coverage.ts\n   574→│   ├── stack.ts\n   575→│   └── ...\n   576→├── lib/                # Shared utilities (domain subdirectories)\n   577→│   ├── stacks/         # Stack provider pattern (Decision 2)\n   578→│   ├── agents/         # Agent driver pattern (Decision 3)\n   579→│   ├── coverage/       # Coverage detection, execution, parsing\n   580→│   ├── docker/         # Docker compose, health, cleanup\n   581→│   ├── observability/  # OTLP instrumentation, backend queries\n   582→│   ├── sync/           # Beads, sprint YAML, story files\n   583→│   ├── state.ts        # Project config (codeharness.local.md)\n   584→│   ├── output.ts       # CLI output helpers\n   585→│   └── templates.ts    # Template interpolation\n   586→├── modules/            # Business logic modules\n   587→│   ├── sprint/         # Sprint state, story selection, progress\n   588→│   │   ├── index.ts\n   589→│   │   ├── state.ts    # Unified sprint-state.json read/write\n   590→│   │   ├── selector.ts # Story prioritization (Tier A/B/C/D)\n   591→│   │   └── progress.ts # Live progress updates\n   592→│   ├── verify/         # Verification orchestration\n   593→│   │   ├── index.ts\n   594→│   │   ├── env.ts      # Generated Dockerfile, container lifecycle\n   595→│   │   ├── runner.ts   # Verification session management\n   596→│   │   └── proof.ts    # Proof parsing and validation\n   597→│   ├── audit/          # Compliance checking\n   598→│   │   ├── index.ts\n   599→│   │   ├── dimensions.ts\n   600→│   │   └── report.ts\n   601→│   ├── observability/  # Static analysis, runtime validation\n   602→│   │   ├── index.ts\n   603→│   │   ├── analyzer.ts\n   604→│   │   ├── runtime.ts\n   605→│   │   └── types.ts\n   606→│   ├── infra/          # Init, docs scaffold, Docker setup\n   607→│   │   ├── index.ts\n   608→│   │   ├── init-project.ts\n   609→│   │   ├── docs-scaffold.ts\n   610→│   │   └── dockerfile-template.ts\n   611→│   ├── review/         # Code review enforcement\n   612→│   └── status/         # Status display logic (moved from command)\n   613→│       ├── index.ts\n   614→│       ├── formatters.ts\n   615→│       ├── endpoints.ts\n   616→│       └── drill-down.ts\n   617→├── types/              # Shared types\n   618→│   └── result.ts       # Result<T> pattern\n   619→└── index.ts            # CLI entry point, command registration\n   620→\n   621→templates/              # All templates (static files, interpolated at runtime)\n   622→├── dockerfiles/\n   623→├── otlp/\n   624→├── compose/\n   625→├── prompts/\n   626→└── docs/\n   627→\n   628→ralph/                  # Agent execution loop (bash)\n   629→├── ralph.sh\n   630→├── drivers/\n   631→└── lib/\n   632→\n   633→patches/                # Enforcement rules\n   634→├── observability/      # Semgrep rules (per-language)\n   635→└── infra/              # Dockerfile rules\n   636→\n   637→hooks/                  # Claude Code plugin hooks\n   638→commands/               # Claude Code plugin commands (markdown)\n   639→skills/                 # Claude Code plugin skills\n   640→knowledge/              # Claude Code plugin knowledge\n   641→```\n   642→\n   643→---\n   644→\n   645→## Implementation Patterns\n   646→\n   647→### Result\\<T\\> — Mandatory for All Module Functions\n   648→\n   649→```typescript\n   650→import { ok, fail, isOk } from '../types/result.js';\n   651→import type { Result } from '../types/result.js';\n   652→\n   653→function doThing(): Result<Data> {\n   654→  if (bad) return fail('reason');\n   655→  return ok(data);\n   656→}\n   657→```\n   658→\n   659→No exceptions for module-level public functions. Commands catch Result.fail and format errors.\n   660→\n   661→### Typed Errors — For Domain-Specific Failures\n   662→\n   663→```typescript\n   664→class BeadsNotInstalledError extends Error { name = 'BeadsNotInstalledError'; }\n   665→class DockerNotAvailableError extends Error { name = 'DockerNotAvailableError'; }\n   666→```\n   667→\n   668→Callers catch specific types, not bare `catch`.\n   669→\n   670→### Stack Provider — Polymorphic Dispatch\n   671→\n   672→```typescript\n   673→const provider = getStackProvider(stack);\n   674→const coverage = provider.detectCoverageConfig(dir);\n   675→const dockerfile = provider.getDockerfileTemplate();\n   676→```\n   677→\n   678→Never `if (stack === 'nodejs')` in consumer code.\n   679→\n   680→### Atomic State Writes\n   681→\n   682→```typescript\n   683→function writeStateAtomic(path: string, data: unknown): void {\n   684→  const tmp = path + '.tmp';\n   685→  writeFileSync(tmp, JSON.stringify(data, null, 2));\n   686→  renameSync(tmp, path);\n   687→}\n   688→```\n   689→\n   690→All state files. No partial writes.\n   691→\n   692→### Template Interpolation\n   693→\n   694→```typescript\n   695→function renderTemplate(templatePath: string, vars: Record<string, string>): string {\n   696→  let content = readFileSync(templatePath, 'utf-8');\n   697→  for (const [key, value] of Object.entries(vars)) {\n   698→    content = content.replaceAll(`{{${key}}}`, value);\n   699→  }\n   700→  return content;\n   701→}\n   702→```\n   703→\n   704→Simple. No template engine dependency.\n   705→\n   706→---\n   707→\n   708→## NFRs (Enforced, Not Aspirational)\n   709→\n   710→| NFR | Rule | Enforcement |\n   711→|-----|------|-------------|\n   712→| NFR1 | No file >300 lines (excluding tests) | CI gate |\n   713→| NFR2 | Result\\<T\\> for all module public functions | Code review checklist |\n   714→| NFR3 | No bare `catch {}` without `// IGNORE:` comment | ESLint rule |\n   715→| NFR4 | No direct stack conditionals outside `src/lib/stacks/` | Boundary test |\n   716→| NFR5 | Commands <100 lines | CI gate |\n   717→| NFR6 | Module imports only through index.ts | Boundary test |\n   718→| NFR7 | Atomic writes for all state files | Code review checklist |\n   719→| NFR8 | All templates in `templates/` directory (not generated in TS) | Convention |\n   720→| NFR9 | Test coverage ≥90% | CI gate |\n   721→\n   722→---\n   723→\n   724→## Migration Strategy\n   725→\n   726→This is NOT a big-bang rewrite. Migration is epic-by-epic:\n   727→\n   728→**Phase 1: Foundation (Epic 10)**\n   729→- Create `src/lib/stacks/` with provider pattern\n   730→- Migrate Node.js, Python, Rust to providers\n   731→- Delete 41 if/else branches across 8 files\n   732→\n   733→**Phase 2: State Consolidation (Epic 11)**\n   734→- Unify sprint-state.json schema\n   735→- Migrate `.story_retries` and `.flagged_stories` into it\n   736→- Make sprint-status.yaml a derived view\n   737→- Add schema versioning\n   738→\n   739→**Phase 3: lib/ Restructuring (Epic 12)**\n   740→- Split oversized files into domain subdirectories\n   741→- Move business logic from commands to modules\n   742→- Add boundary tests\n   743→\n   744→**Phase 4: Agent Abstraction (Epic 13)**\n   745→- Create AgentDriver interface\n   746→- Wrap Ralph behind it\n   747→- Move ralph-specific parsing into ralph driver\n   748→\n   749→**Phase 5: Process Fixes (Epic 14)**\n   750→- Retro-to-sprint pipeline\n   751→- Tech debt gate\n   752→- Docker pre-check, time budget, subagent enforcement\n   753→- Observability backend choice\n   754→- Verification environment generation\n   755→\n   756→**Phase 6: Enforcement (Epic 15)**\n   757→- CI file size gate\n   758→- ESLint no-empty-catch rule\n   759→- Boundary test for stack conditionals\n   760→- Template migration\n   761→\n   762→Each phase produces working software. No phase depends on all other phases being complete. The order is: foundations → state → structure → abstraction → process → enforcement.\n   763→\n   764→---\n   765→\n   766→## Validation\n   767→\n   768→### Current Architecture Gaps Addressed\n   769→\n   770→| Gap | Decision |\n   771→|-----|----------|\n   772→| 5+ state files, no sync | Decision 1 (Unified State) |\n   773→| 41 stack conditionals | Decision 2 (Stack Provider) |\n   774→| 28 files coupled to Ralph | Decision 3 (Agent Abstraction) |\n   775→| lib/ is a flat dumping ground | Decision 4 (lib/ Restructuring) |\n   776→| Hardcoded VictoriaMetrics | Decision 5 (Backend Choice) |\n   777→| Retro items never actioned | Decision 6 (Retro-to-Sprint Pipeline) |\n   778→| 53 bare catch blocks | Decision 7 (Error Handling) |\n   779→| Commands contain business logic | Decision 8 (Thin Commands) |\n   780→| Two template systems | Decision 9 (Template Unification) |\n   781→| Under-provisioned verify containers | Decision 10 (Stack-Aware Provisioning) |\n   782→| Missing process gates | Decision 11 (Process Enforcement) |\n   783→| 12 files over 300 lines | Decision 12 (File Size CI Gate) |\n   784→\n   785→### Readiness: YES — with phased migration\n   786→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014osh4xMtXKp3eoJrCF5J4g","session_id":"ec2bf7d9-1cd3-4665-9804-65790a3eadb3","uuid":"4d05be1a-f87c-45c2-8383-73ef4d0ac1ab","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:56:58.805Z"}
