{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ARDMJdo7LDpJboWrzKfH84","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here is the summary of what was implemented:\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/utils.ts` — shared helpers (`readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps`) extracted from `stack-detect.ts`\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — replaced all 15 stub methods with full implementations extracted from `stack-detect.ts`, `coverage.ts`, `otlp.ts`, `dockerfile-template.ts`, and `docs-scaffold.ts`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/nodejs.test.ts` — replaced stub validation tests with 64 comprehensive tests covering all methods, all AC scenarios, and edge cases\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-2-nodejs-provider.md` — status set to `review`, all 18 ACs and 17 tasks marked complete\n\n**Test results:** 64/64 nodejs tests pass. Full suite: 120 files, 3253 tests, 0 regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **OtlpResult type mismatch:** The `OtlpResult` in `stacks/types.ts` (`{ success, packagesInstalled, error? }`) differs from the one in `otlp.ts` (`{ status, packages_installed, start_script_patched, env_vars_configured, error? }`). The provider uses the stacks/types version as designed. Story 10-5 will need to reconcile these when consumers migrate to using the provider.\n- **`patchStartScript` is optional on the interface but implemented on NodejsProvider.** This is correct per the types (`patchStartScript?` in StackProvider), but consumers calling `provider.patchStartScript?.(dir)` need the optional chaining.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors:** ~50 type errors exist in other test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, deps.test.ts, etc.) unrelated to this story. They appear to be from interface changes that haven't been backfilled into tests.\n-