{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AYUK9c5QWsnPVHthUcsHao","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"121 test files, 3267 tests, all passing. Zero regressions.\n\n---\n\n**Review Complete.**\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-2-nodejs-provider.md`\n**Story Status:** updated to `verifying`\n**Issues Found:** 2 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM, 1 LOW\n**Issues Fixed:** 2 HIGH, 2 MEDIUM (all HIGH and MEDIUM fixed)\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` -- Fixed `parseTestOutput()` vitest and jest regex to capture skipped counts\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/nodejs.test.ts` -- Added 5 new tests (skipped count parsing, malformed JSON in patchStartScript)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/utils.test.ts` -- Created. 9 tests covering `readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-2-nodejs-provider.md` -- Status changed to `verifying`\n\n**Coverage results:** 97.09% overall (target: 90%), all 128 files above 80% per-file floor.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- **HIGH** -- `parseTestOutput()` vitest regex did not capture skipped test count; `total` was wrong when vitest reported skipped tests (e.g., `Tests  12 passed | 3 failed | 1 skipped` returned total=15 instead of 16, skipped=0 instead of 1)\n- **HIGH** -- `parseTestOutput()` jest regex failed to capture `total` when `skipped` appeared between `passed` and `total` in jest output (e.g., `Tests: 3 failed, 12 passed, 2 skipped, 17 total` returned total=15 instead of 17). Rewrote jest parser to extract each field independently.\n- **MEDIUM** -- `utils.ts` was at 70.58% statement coverage (below 80% floor) because `readTextSafe()` was completely untested. Added dedicated test file.\n- **MEDIUM** -- `nodejs.ts` line 194 (catch branch in `patchStartScript` for malformed JSON) was untested. Added test.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `utils.ts` line 24 (catch branch in `readTextSafe`) remains uncovered at 93.33% -- would require mocking `readFileSync` to throw after `existsSync` succeeds, which is an extremely unlikely race condition. Not worth the test complexity.\n- `nodejs.ts` lines 173-177 and 300 show as uncovered in branch coverage -- these are the `catch` blocks in `patchStartScript` and `parseCoverageReport` error paths that require filesystem-level failures to trigger. Coverage is 100% on statements.\n- `registry.ts` at 94.73% -- lines 75 and 120 uncovered. Not part of this story (story 10-1).\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No integration test for `installOtlp()` success path (would require actual npm install in test environment -- correctly skipped as unit tests only)\n- `readTextSafe` catch branch (filesystem permission errors) not testable without mocking\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The extraction pattern is clean and matches the source files faithfully. The `OtlpResult` type in `stacks/types.ts` differs structurally from `otlp.ts` (uses `success/packagesInstalled` vs `status/packages_installed`). This is intentional per story 10-2 tech notes and will be reconciled in story 10-5.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a71245e97f40032ad (use SendMessage with to: 'a71245e97f40032ad' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 69028\ntool_uses: 47\nduration_ms: 317554</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec2bf7d9-1cd3-4665-9804-65790a3eadb3","uuid":"24778071-1110-4254-b435-7636e1c2f149","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:10:23.832Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-2-nodejs-provider.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure