tput()` vitest regex did not capture skipped test count; `total` was wrong when vitest reported skipped tests (e.g., `Tests  12 passed | 3 failed | 1 skipped` returned total=15 instead of 16, skipped=0 instead of 1)\n- **HIGH** -- `parseTestOutput()` jest regex failed to capture `total` when `skipped` appeared between `passed` and `total` in jest output (e.g., `Tests: 3 failed, 12 passed, 2 skipped, 17 total` returned total=15 instead of 17). Rewrote jest parser to extract each field independently.\n- **MEDIUM** -- `utils.ts` was at 70.58% statement coverage (below 80% floor) because `readTextSafe()` was completely untested. Added dedicated test file.\n- **MEDIUM** -- `nodejs.ts` line 194 (catch branch in `patchStartScript` for malformed JSON) was untested. Added test.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `utils.ts` line 24 (catch branch in `readTextSafe`) remains uncovered at 93.33% -- would require mocking `readFileSync` to throw after `existsSync` succeeds, which is an extremely unlikely race condition. Not worth the test complexity.\n- `nodejs.ts` lines 173-177 and 300 show as uncovered in branch coverage -- these are the `catch` blocks in `patchStartScript` and `parseCoverageReport` error paths that require filesystem-level failures to trigger. Coverage is 100% on statements.\n- `registry.ts` at 94.73% -- lines 75 and 120 uncovered. Not part of this story (story 10-1).\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No integration test for `installOtlp()` success path (would require actual npm install in test environment -- correctly skipped as unit tests only)\n- `readTextSafe` catch branch (filesystem permission errors) not testable without mocking\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The extraction pattern is clean and matches the source files faithfully. The `OtlpResult` type in `stacks/types.ts` differs structurally from `otlp.ts` (uses `success/packagesInstalled` vs `status/packages_installed`). This is intentional per story 10-2 tech notes and will be rec