{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Kwd9ExxmfYnzvk5h7SsvTi","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24 (session 2)\n     2→\n     3→### 10-2-nodejs-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T07:58Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Observation:** Existing `10-2-nodejs-provider.md` had minimal 3-AC version; overwrote with detailed 18-AC version with task breakdown and verification tags.\n     6→- **Observation:** `CoverageToolInfo` type mismatch between `stacks/types.ts` (`{ tool, configFile? }`) and `coverage.ts` (`{ tool, runCommand, reportFormat }`). Story notes this — reconciliation deferred to story 10-5.\n     7→- **Risk:** Epic AC3 says \"remove all Node.js if/else branches from consumers\" but incremental migration strategy defers this to 10-5. Replaced with AC18 (zero regressions) to match actual intent.\n     8→- **Problems:** None.\n     9→- **Workarounds:** None.\n    10→\n    11→### 10-2-nodejs-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T08:02Z)\n    12→\n    13→- **OtlpResult type mismatch:** `stacks/types.ts` (`{ success, packagesInstalled, error? }`) differs from `otlp.ts` (`{ status, packages_installed, start_script_patched, env_vars_configured, error? }`). Provider uses stacks/types version. Reconciliation deferred to 10-5.\n    14→- **`patchStartScript` optional on interface but implemented.** Consumers need optional chaining `provider.patchStartScript?.(dir)`.\n    15→- **Pre-existing TS errors:** ~50 type errors in other test files (bridge, run, deps, etc.) unrelated to this story.\n    16→- **Consumer branches not removed** (by design per spec). Story 10-5 handles migration.\n    17→- **Test results:** 64/64 nodejs tests pass. Full suite: 3253 tests, 0 regressions.\n    18→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec2bf7d9-1cd3-4665-9804-65790a3eadb3","uuid":"88bbfc11-e555-435f-b725-da0d688ba43a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:10:28.319Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24 (session 2)\n\n### 10-2-nodejs-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T07:58Z)\n\n- **Observation:** Existing `10-2-nodejs-provider.md` had minimal 3-AC version; overwrote with detailed 18-AC version with task breakdown and verification tags.\n- **Observation:** `CoverageToolInfo` type mismatch between `stacks/types.ts` (`{ tool, configFile? }`) and `coverage.ts` (`{ tool, runCommand, reportFormat }`). Story notes this — reconciliation deferred to story 10-5.\n- **Risk:** Epic AC3 says \"remove all Node.js if/else branches from consumers\" but incremental migration strategy defers this to 10-5. Replaced with AC18 (zero regressions) to match actual intent.\n- **Problems:** None.\n- **Workarounds:** None.\n\n### 10-2-nodejs-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T08:02Z)\n\n- **OtlpResult type mismatch:** `stacks/types.ts` (`{ success, packagesInstalled, error? }`) differs from `otlp.ts` (`{ status, packages_installed, start_script_patched, env_vars_configured, error? }`). Provider uses stacks/types version. Reconciliation deferred to 10-5.\n- **`patchStartScript` optional on interface but implemented.** Consumers need optional chaining `provider.patchStartScript?.(dir)`.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors:** ~50 type errors in other test files (bridge, run, deps, etc.) unrelated to this story.\n- **Consumer branches not removed** (by design per spec). Story 10-5 handles migration.\n- **Test results:** 64/64 nodejs tests pass. Full suite: 3253 tests, 0 regressions.\n","numLines":18,"startLine":1,"totalLines":18}}}
